    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Artificial earthen mounds, usually burial mounds, that are round and dome-shaped, sometimes with a very narrow, pointed top. Such mounds were especially prevalent with early indigenous inhabitants of midwest North America.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
